item.title: Need Help! :confused:
item.dc:creator: @marcbob marcbob
item.description:
@marcbob wrote:

There could be a lot of things causing the error_gamejs5connect error. It means the client can’t connect to any server that it was set to and by that I mean it couldn’t find your IP hosting the server.

Possible problems:

  1. You didn’t put your ip in the client correctly and/or compile it correctly.
  2. You did not portforward correctly so connects are being blocked to your IP. I suggest searching in the tutorials section on how to port forward. When I find a helpful tutorial for you I will post it here.

EDIT: Here are some tutorials on port forwarding: http://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/topic,522617.msg3800867.html#msg3800867

Just scroll down to the section with a lot of portforwarding tutorials. The other thing I recommend is you turn off your firewall so it doesn’t block connections.
